Title: Governance Review — ODNI Staffing Directive / Bill Pulte Reference  
Author: Shayan Aboutalebi  
Date: 2026-06-06

EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
AP reported that President Donald Trump stated he wanted his acting director of national intelligence, Bill Pulte, to reduce staffing at the Office of the Director of National Intelligence (ODNI), describing the organization as too large and indicating intent to initiate personnel cuts. The report also states he would not formally nominate Pulte for the permanent DNI position.

Bill Pulte is identified in reporting as Director of the Federal Housing Finance Agency and chairman of Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac since 2025.

FACTUAL CONTEXT
The comments were reportedly made aboard Air Force One on June 5, 2026. The statements focused on reducing ODNI staffing levels following prior restructuring during the administration’s term. The intent described is organizational downsizing rather than procedural execution.

REVIEW FRAMEWORK
- This document records publicly reported statements only.
- No operational directive is executed or implied.
- Employment actions require formal legal and administrative process.
- No bypass of statutory or HR frameworks is authorized or represented.

RISK CLASSIFICATION
- Governance sensitivity: Medium
- Legal execution risk: High if misapplied
- Operational authority: None assigned

STATUS
Archival review entry only. No action executed.
